JIRA OBJGEN1-950 Ceph: report RGW concurrent connection or other data to SRE

Developer: @vgoot
Code Review: @sung @bzymka

[Description]
Start reporting metrics from simple_throttler into Prometheus to gain per-RGW observability of the current number of connections waiting in the queue, and rejected connections resulting in 503 errors.

[Grafana]
TITLE: QLen by RGW
METRIC: ceph_simple_throttler_outstanding
TYPE: gauge
DESC: current number of accepted connections waiting in Q by RGW
QUERY: sum by (rgw_host) (label_replace(ceph_simple_throttler_outstanding * on (instance_id) group_left (ceph_daemon) ceph_rgw_metadata, "rgw_host", "$1", "ceph_daemon", "rgw.(.*)"))

TITLE: Dropped connections by RGW
METRIC: ceph_simple_throttler_throttle
TYPE: counter
DESC: connections rejected with 503 by RGW
QUERY: sum by (rgw_host) (label_replace(rate(ceph_simple_throttler_throttle[60s]) * on (instance_id) group_left (ceph_daemon) ceph_rgw_metadata, "rgw_host", "$1", "ceph_daemon", "rgw.(.*)"))

[File Changed]
src/rgw/rgw_dmclock_async_scheduler.h
src/rgw/rgw_dmclock_scheduler_ctx.cc
